Package: heatindexbr
Title: Heat Index Mapping for the Brazilian Semiarid Region
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Antônio", "Campos Neto",
           email = "antonio.camposneto9@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0009-0007-3844-3869"))
Description: Provides pre-computed Heat Index (Rothfusz 1990) rasters for
    the Brazilian Semiarid region (1,477 municipalities, Res.
    CONDEL/SUDENE 176/2024) at four synoptic hours (00h, 09h, 15h, 21h
    local time) and tools for spatial extraction by municipality name,
    IBGE code, or user-supplied shapefile. Data are hosted on Zenodo
    (doi:10.5281/zenodo.20942619) and downloaded on first use to a
    local cache. Interpolated using External Drift Kriging with altitude
    and ERA5-Land covariates. Future versions will include monthly,
    daily, and hourly products.
